    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class='post'>
<div><br/><p>While using windows we get ^M characters in files that will get displayed when you open files on unix machines.</p><br/><p>To remove such ^M characters,</p><br/><p>Install dos2unix package using</p><br/><blockquote><p>sudo apt-get install sysutils</p></blockquote><br/><p>Convert individual file</p><br/><blockquote><p>dos2unix file_path</p></blockquote><br/><p>Run following command to convert recursively all the files inside directory.</p><br/><blockquote><br/><pre>find . -type f -exec dos2unix {} \;<br/></pre><br/></blockquote><br/></div><br/><div id="_mcePaste" style="overflow:hidden;position:absolute;left:-10000px;top:7px;width:1px;height:1px;"><br/><pre class="alt2" style="border:1px inset;overflow:auto;width:640px;height:34px;text-align:left;margin:0;padding:6px;">sudo apt-get install sysutils</pre><br/></div></div>

